  • Field Details

    • DELETE_FILE_THRESHOLD

      public static final String DELETE_FILE_THRESHOLD
      The minimum number of deletes that needs to be associated with a data file for it to be considered for rewriting. If a data file has this number of deletes or more, it will be rewritten regardless of its file size determined by SizeBasedFileRewriter.MIN_FILE_SIZE_BYTES and SizeBasedFileRewriter.MAX_FILE_SIZE_BYTES. If a file group contains a file that satisfies this condition, the file group will be rewritten regardless of the number of files in the file group determined by SizeBasedFileRewriter.MIN_INPUT_FILES.

      Defaults to Integer.MAX_VALUE, which means this feature is not enabled by default.
